gomodel:SYNGO_916  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors use an antibody specific for PLC B4 in immunoelectron microscopy studies. PLC B4 was detected at the postsynaptic ER in both pre-embedding EM(Figure 5). In line with a localization to the ER, in subcellular fractionation, PLC-B4 was detected in a fraction that is also enriched in IP3R (Figure 6).\n\nThe antibody against PLC B4 is verified by western blot against PLC B4 knockout (Figure 1).. Experimental description: Adult C57BL mice at 2-3 months of age were used in the present\nstudy, with the exception of ICR mice for immunoprecipitation." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-22" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_916" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

